705087f-b.title: Brooklyn: Jamaica Avenue - Ashford Street
705087f-b.text:
(1)
Jamaica Ave., north side, opposite Ashford Street, in Highland
Park, showing the Isaac Cornell Schenck house.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPPODUCED.
(2)
The same, another view. (This house formerly on the north side
of Jamaica Ave., between Monroe Street and Eldert Ave., was built in
either 1760 or 1705 and remodeled on several occasions; once in 1792,
by Isaac Cornell, and again in 1811, by Judge Schenck).
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPPODUCED.
(3)
TThe same, showing a closer view of the house.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
For additional data see 'The New York Herald Tribune,' April
6, 1941.
